			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Here is some info on Avatars and Spirits as I see many people want to be come summoners this might be useful for you.
<br />

<br />
First off, Avatars are summons that you have to obtain by defeating the Prime Avatar in a battle. The Battles will require you to be level 60+ and have level 7+ fame in the town you wish to obtain the avatar from. Except Fenrir, he is tougher and will need a party of 70+ to take down. In avatar battles you cannot have an alliance, so only 6 people, you will need a white mage with the appropriate bar spells (example barblizzardra for Shiva) and have at least 150 enhancing magic, you will also need the carol songs from bards, such as Ice Carol (they stack).
<br />

<br />
In order to enter the battle everyone in the party must have the quest started or have done it before. You do not need to be on your summoner job in order to do the battle.
<br />

<br />
After an avatar is defeated you talk to the NPC who gave the quest for a list of available rewards, if you select none, it will give you the pact so you can summon that avatar, if you do it a second time or more you can select an item of your choice or 10,000 gil.
<br />

<br />
This is important for those who wish to do the summoner quests repeated, they ARE repeatable. After you choose your reward from the NPC you must wait 24 real life hours to do the quest again, ALSO you must talk to the NPC again to start it, AS IF it were your first time to do the quest.
<br />

<br />
You CAN be level 1 Summoner and have all of the avatars spirits when you begin playing it, or you can level the Summoner up some with carbuncle and obtain avatars later on as you go to add to your list of avatars, either way works fine.
<br />

<br />
Avatars each have unique abilities called Blood Pacts that they can do once per minute. The higher the level you are the more abilities open up, like a normal job. They are specific to the avatar, carbuncle gets healing ruby at level 1, at level 5 he gets poison nails... Shiva gets Axe kick at level 1, at level 10 she gets blizzard 2...
<br />

<br />
Spirits are just somewhat like avatars, they are something you cast to have attack monsters. They take more mp to keep out, but only take 2 seconds to cast versus 5 for an avatar. 
<br />

<br />
Spirits are obtained by quests and Burning Circle Notorious monsters (BCNM) battles. 
<br />

<br />
You can get Fire Spirit at BCNM 40, Light Spirit at BCNM 50, I don't know where to obtain an Ice Spirit or others, some are dropped off yagudos I believe. 
<br />

<br />
Spirits aren't that wonderful in the lower levels, your avatars will be better. At higher levels spirits can use Ancient Magic which is very nice. 
<br />

<br />
When you obtain a siprit pact , lets say you purchase one, you say use and learn it like a normal scroll. You can then cast and recast that spirit as many times as you want.
<br />

<br />
Black mages get ancient magic, things like Freeze , or Flood which do huge mass damage. Part of the problem also is you dont have as many commands with spirits, they kinda do their own thing when you say attack. 
<br />

<br />

<br />
The avatars and the towns you get them from are 
<br />

<br />
Carbuncle is free when you finish the Summoner quest
<br />
Fenrir (Windurst Waters) NPC = Leepe Hoppe (Really Hard)
<br />
Leviathan (Norg) NPC = Edal-Tahdal (Hard)
<br />
Ramuh (Mhaura) NPC = Ripapa (Medium)
<br />
Ifrit (Kazham) NPC = Ronta-Onta (Medium)
<br />
Garuda (Rabao) NPC = Agado-Pugadoka (Hard)
<br />
Shiva (North San d'Oria) NPC = Gulmama (Medium)
<br />
Titan (Port Bastok) NPC = Juroro (Medium)
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
There are also 9 levels of fame, you need at least level 7 fame to start the quest for an avatar battle.
<br />

<br />
Fame info 
<br />

<br />
Every character in FFXI has 6 different fame groups. Each of these fame groups are tracked separately from each other, although your level in one can affect your level in another, as you will see. 
<br />

<br />
Here are the different fame groups. 
<br />

<br />
San d'Oria Fame 
<br />

<br />
This fame level measures quests done in the city of San d'Oria. 
<br />

<br />
Bastok Fame 
<br />

<br />
This fame level measures quests done in the city of Bastok. 
<br />

<br />
Windurst Fame 
<br />

<br />
This fame level measures quests done in the cities of Windurst, Mhaura and Khazam. 
<br />

<br />
Selbina Fame 
<br />

<br />
This fame level measures quests done in the cities of Selbina and Rabao. 
<br />
This fame level is also increased by the average of your San d'Oria and Bastok levels. 
<br />

<br />
Jeuno Fame 
<br />

<br />
This fame level measures quests done in the city of Jeuno. 
<br />
This fame level is also increased by the average of your San d'Oria, Bastok and windurst levels. 
<br />

<br />
Tenshodo Fame 
<br />

<br />
This fame level measures quests done for Tenshodo HQ in Lower Jeuno and Tenshodo Branch in Bastok Port. This fame level also counts quests done for The Brugaire Consortium in San d'Oria Port, and for Nanaa Mihgo's thieves in Windurst. This fame level also includes quests done in the city of Norg 
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
This is just some basic info if you have any questions you may ask away.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
