			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Just wanted to add some info from my experiences:
<br />

<br />
Getting fame can be a long and tedious process.  However, attaining a lot of the fame you need to open up the avatar quests, isn't all that bad.
<br />

<br />
Windurst:
<br />
You can do the repeatable Bastore Sardines Quest.  Turn in 1 Bastore Sardine to (I wish I knew her name) the girl standing at the dock at the fishing guild in Windurst Port.  However, you have to zone out before you turn in more.  Good ways to handle this:   Some people put on BLM and warp everytime to the Windurst Port Mog House and run back.  Or you can use THF Flee.  
<br />

<br />
Bastok, Sandoria and Rabao:
<br />
Turn in 2500-3000 cabbages to the old man near the sheep pen in Selbina.  You turn them in 5 at at time without a need to zone.  If you buy the cabbages from a vendor, you wind up losing only 10k to get max fame in each of these 3 towns.  I don't have solid numbers on fame level 7.  Turning in 3000 will put you over the top though <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
Tenshodo/Norg:
<br />
You can either farm or buy a ridiculous amount of Yagudo Necklaces and turn them into Nanaa Mihgo in Windurst Woods.  If you buy them on the AH, you will lose a lot of gil, but you have to pay to get fame.  Otherwise, slaughter Yagudo in Giddeus with THF Treasure Hunter to speed it up.  
<br />

<br />
I'm not sure about Kazham fame, but Max Windy fame may give you max Kazham fame.
<br />

<br />
You do not need Jeuno fame to attain avatars.  However, if you have max fame in Windurst, SanDoria and Bastok, you will have max fame in Jeuno.  
<br />

<br />
If you elect to obtain an item from the avatar fight, rather than the summon, you will receive 10k gil or a Rare/Ex item.  So, don't plan on going along for the avatar fight for the loot unless you need it.  
<br />

<br />
A summoner equipped with most of the avatars is a very useful party member.  The party buffs that the avatars give the party are extremely useful.
<br />

<br />
I'll just run through the "good ones"  <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" /> 
<br />
25 - Garuda, Aerial Armor (Party Blink)
<br />
28 - Shiva, Frost Armor (Group Ice spikes)
<br />
31 - Ramuh, Rolling Thunder (Enthunder on party)
<br />
36 - Garuda, Whispering Wind (Similar to Curaga)
<br />
39 - Shiva, Sleepga
<br />
42 - Ramuh, Lightning Armor (Group Shock Spikes)
<br />
46 - Titan, Earthen Ward (Group Stoneskin) 
<br />
47 - Leviathan, Spring Water (Like Curaga II plus removes status ailments but not those that Erase and Viruna do)
<br />
48 - Garuda, Hastega (Party haste!)
<br />

<br />
There are more, but that is just a taste, and doesn't include Fenrir.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
